inn1.comm: full toss to begin with outside off and Finch punches it down the ground past mid-off to collect four
bit of movement as this one's on length on middle and coming in, it's flicked off the pads wide of mid-on where Anwar Ali dives and takes some time to pick up and throw to let them take two
length delivery angling away from outside off, left alone
on length and angling across again, much better from Irfan and Finch defends it down
appeal for lbw as it pitched around leg and was short of length. But there was an inside edge
on length on middle and off with the angle, finch defends it back
full and nearly in the block hole outside off, whipped down to mid-on off the back foot
swinging into the pads and it's full too, Warner helps it along with the flick and finds the gap through midwicket for his first four
swings it in again, from length towards middle stump, Warner hops back and tucks to short midwicket
length delivery with a bit of inswing from outside off, thick inside edge off the defence goes to the leg side
swings one away now but it was a bit too short and wide and Warner left it easily
the last ball swings in from well outside off, Warner chases and gets an inside edge to fine leg. It wasn't too far from the stumps and he keeps strike
length delivery coming in towards off stump, Warner defends off the back foot
full and wide, Warner goes down on a knee and drives it through the covers for two more
swings it a touch now towards the pads and it's full, Warner flicks it late with the wrists to fine leg
full and wide, Finch doesn't move much and drives it to extra cover
touch shorter, but it's still full and wide and Finch gets into better position by leaning forward and getting on top of it to drive it for four
length delivery angling across from length, keeps a bit low and Finch blocks it
outswing for the length delivery from outside off, thick outside edge goes to third man for one
outside leg and towards the pads, flicked with the wrists past midwicket for two
angles it away from outside off, Finch leans forward and defends it
bit too wide outside off but it's just inside the wide line as Finch lets it go
length delivery shaping away from off, finch isn't sure which way it will swing. He stays back to defend and gets an edge to the leg side
stays on the back foot and defends the away-going delivery on the leg side. Much better over from Tanvir
length delivery outside off, Warner stays back and defends it
brings it a touch closer to off stump and Warner defends again

he finds the gap with a drive, it was pitched up outside off, Warner drove with a step down the pitch past cover point. Shehzad was on the chase and did very well to dive forward and stop but the ball eventually got there
brings it in from just back of length towards off stump, Warner defends off the back foot
wider outside off, the ball stops a bit as Warner checks his shot a bit while defending
back of length and angling in, clipped to midwicket off the toes
short of length from outside leg, tucked off the back foot to midwicket
fuller on leg stump and that's flicked firmly with the wrists right between midwicket and mid-on for a powerful four
length delivery angling across from length, defends with a forward lean
touch shorter and just outside off with the angle, punched to short cover
back of length on middle and off, Finch goes back in the crease and defends it back
teasing length outside off, Finch puts a foot forward tentatively and pushes to point
back of length and heading towards leg, clipped down to fine leg
bit of inswing from length outside off, Warner defends tentatively
he's in great touch, Warner! Gets width outside off and drives it authoritatively past short cover from the middle of the bat for four
full on the other side this time, into the pads and that's flicked with the rolling wrists over midwicket for another four
back of length towards leg stump, clipped down to fine leg for one more
he continues to bowl full but Finch drives it straight to point off the front foot
holds its line after pitching outside off on length, Warner defends towards cover
persists with the line outside off, defends it to short cover
goes a bit shorter outside off, punched to cover by Warner
hint of outswing outside off, Warner taps it to point where Fawad gets to it quickly and denies them the single
length delivery close to the off stump, Warner defends it back
touch fuller outside off, Warner defends again and that's a maiden from Tanvir
on length outside off, it's pushed down on the off side
outswing outside off, it was on length and kept a bit low as Finch looked to cut it
bangs it in shorter around off and Finch punches it back, Anwar gets a hand to it
inswing from back of length outside off, pushed down gently to mid-on and they take a quick single knowing Irfan is the fielder. And he gets a direct hit, but Finch is safe
pushed uppishly, it was in the air and wide of mid-off after the ball pitched on short of length with the angle. But it went in the gap and they got two
slower delivery outside off and it's full enough for Warner to drive it nicely between cover mid-off for four more
flighted outside off, pushed towards point off the front foot
on length outside off again, touch flatter and Finch pushed it again with a forward lean
comes down the track now, he's hit well outside off but Babar goes for a long lbw appeal
drifts one in towards middle, Finch defends it on the leg side
slightly slower on middle stump, Finch leans forward and blocks
drifts the full delivery in towards middle stump, it's pushed down to long-off for one
slightly back of length on the off stump, Finch stays back and defends
back of length outside off, punched towards the covers

practice catch for mid-on! Anwar Ali breaks the stand. It was short of length outside off, Finch didn't move much and was maybe it two minds to punch it down the ground or clear mid-on and ended up chipping it to Irfan at mid-on. Finch's poor run on the tour continues
on length outside off, Smith leans forward and gets an edge on the pads
fullish outside off, Smith takes a step across and whips to mid-on
back of length outside off, Smith moves across and turns it to deep midwicket
flighted on off, pushed down gently to mid-on for a quick single
takes a step down to take it on the full and drives to long-on
uses his feet very well to not let it turn and he whips it from outside off with the wrists, wide of mid-on for four
wider outside off, Smioth stays back and gets an edge on the pads
drifts it down the leg side and Smith helps it towards the fine leg area where there's nobody as Shafiq had to dive to keep it in but it went for four
uses his feet again and whips it past midwicket in the gap, he's middling everything and they get two more
short of length outside off, tapped to sweeper cover easily for one
back of length outside off, Smith stays back and defends
goes a touch shorter and Smith defends it gently to short cover
angles in towards middle and leg from back of length, tucked to deep midwicket for one
on length from around leg stump, turned to midwicket off the pads
on length on middle and angling away, tapped towards cover and they get a quick single as the fielder misfields
turns it in from off stump, Warner defends it back
goes a touch outside off, Warner goes back and punches it back
leans forward this time and blocks the delivery from outside off
length delivery turning in from off, helped with the turn to deep midwicket
drifts in in towards length outside off, Smith defends it back
drifting in further towards middle stump now, punched back off the back foot
length delivery outside off, pushed down to mid-off
outswing from leg stump and the extra bounce surprises Warner a bit as he defends
short of length from middle and angling away, jabbed off the back foot towards deep midwicket in the gap for two
on the pads this time and it's clipped to deep midwicket for one
back of length outside off, Smith defends it off the back foot
shorter outside the off stump and it's punched to mid-off
comes down the track to drive the ball from outside off, it wasn't full at off but he got enough and found the gap between cover and mid-off for four. Umar Akmal chased but lost
turns it in towards off stump, he defends off the back foot
goes back in the crease and turns to deep midwicket for one
comes down a step and flicks to mid-on
flighted around off stump, he defends it back
uses his feet again and drives to mid-on
back of length outside off, taps it late to third man for one
back of length on middle and leg, turned with the wrists to deep midwicket
on length with some room outside off, guides it late to third man for another
chance for a run out! On length around off, whipped to midwicket and Warner wants one, sets off, the fielder gets the throw in but it's not a direct hit and Warner dives desperately
on length outside off, defends it on the off side
cuts in in from outside off, Smith stays back and defends
slog-sweep, and that's been hit extremely well. It was full on off stump, and Warner sinks to one knee and swats that high over deep midwicket to bring up his half-century
a bit of flight on off stump, drops onto a good length, and Warner defends watchfully off the front foot
a touch short, worked off the pads towards square leg
on the pads once more, tucked away to deep midwicket
down the pitch, whipped from outside off to wide long-on
back of a length outside off, worked to short midwicket with a lot of bottom hand
short, and it's pulled from outside off towards the straight midwicket boundary. Maqsood covers a lot of ground from deep square leg to stop that
back of a length outside off, punched to short cover
length ball, angling in towards off stump, Smith comes forward and pushes it wide of short cover, Fawad dives to his left to stop the ball
on the pads, clipped away to deep backward square leg. The throw nutmegs the keeper, and the point fielder is luckily in place to save the overthrows, because the ball was travelling very quickly
length ball outside off, may have been the slower ball, defended off the front foot
shuffles across and works this from middle stump down to deep backward square leg
full on middle and leg, driven wide of long on
full again, on middle stump, driven to long-off
quickish length ball, straightens towards off stump, defended carefully off the back foot
tossed up outside off, pushed to long-off
down the pitch now, and lovely wrist-work to whip that from outside off, into the big gap to the left of deep square leg
quick and full on the stumps, defended down the pitch
looks to drag a length ball from wide outside off and smash it over mid-on, mishits it and sends it rolling along the ground towards that fielder
shortish ball, rising towards the stomach, Warner gets off his feet and works it away to the right of deep backward square leg
fuller now, angling in towards middle stump, defended towards short midwicket
slower ball, comes in from outside off. Warner lets it come to him and defends with a straight bat
back of a length outside off, pulled, not timed very well, to square leg
back of a length, angling across. Smith shuffles across his crease and works that from outside off towards midwicket
goes back to a fairly full ball on the stumps, works it with the turn towards midwicket
slower now, a little leg-sideish, and he looks to clip it off his legs, only gets a bit of pad on it down to fine leg
full on middle and leg, clipped to short midwicket

and Lala strikes! That was much slower than the previous ball, and it dropped on Warner, on off stump, and he pushed at it and lobbed the ball straight back to the bowler, at a nice, catchable waist height
back of a length on middle stump, worked to midwicket from deep in the crease
a bit of width outside off, but it isn't quite short enough to cut, hit straight to short cover
back of a length, and he stands tall and works it off his hips towards deep backward square leg
got him! That was a length ball, angling away outside off, and Bailey followed it and sliced it straight to the man at backward point
back of a length, on off stump, defended towards point
back of a length outside off, Maxwell lets it come to him and steers it away to third man
walks across the stumps, and works this back of a length ball from outside off towards square leg
slower ball outside off, Smith lets it go through to the keeper
angled in towards leg stump, a bit of turn, and Maxwell defends with the spin into the off side
short ball, and he clubs it away from outside off down to long-on
down the pitch nowm driven inside-out to deep cover point
length ball on middle and leg, defended off the front foot towards short cover
low full-toss on middle stump, whipped wristily to midwicket
full on leg stump, clipped to midwicket
back of a length on off stump, defended towards short cover
back of a length outside off, didn't come on at all, and Smith, who was looking to punch through the covers, ended up punching it back to the bowler
back of a length, worked from outside off with a deft flick of the wrist towards square leg
back of a length, angling across, chopped away to the right of third man
angled across again, and Maxwell looks to steer that away with an open face, gets an outside edge but it drops safely short of Sarfraz
short, a bit of width, cut firmly to the right of third man
shortish ball outside off, steered away wide of backward point
tossed up, and Smith was a little early on the shot, but adjusted to check his drive down to long-off
full, worked from middle and off towards midwicket
back of a length on middle stump, tucked away to the left of short fine leg
full and wide, comes forward and chips it over cover
quickish length ball on off stump, defended back to the bowler
back of a length on off stump, punched away to deep cover point
back of a length, clipped from off stump towards short midwicket
shuffles across, tucks it away from an off-stump line down to deep midwicket
stays back to a length ball on the stumps, and has to jam his bat down hurriedly to prevent it from hitting his pads
loopy slower ball on a yorker length just outside off, jams his bat down and squeezes it away backward of point
length ball outside off, driven to deep cover point
quickish length ball outside off, defended towards point
short, a bit of width, chopped away to the left of deep cover
full-toss on the stumps, and he swats it away contemptuously over midwicket, one bounce and over the rope
full on leg stump, clipped to the left of short fine leg
full outside off, driven down to long-off
full, a bit of width, and that's a beautifully caressed drive through extra cover. Deep cover runs to his right and stops it with his boot. Not sure who the fielder was. Babar, maybe?
offcutter, comes back in towards off stump from just back of a length. Maxwell waits on it and chops it away towards third man
back of a length outside off, punched to deep point with a straight bat
back of a length outside off, dabbed away to third man
back of a length, angling in towards off stump, defended towards short cover
comes in off the pitch towards off stump again, Smith shuffles across and works it towards deep square leg
back of a length again, outside off, he's been bowling there right through this over, and Smith comes half-forward and steers it away towards deep point
looks to stride down the pitch but it's a little too quick for that, defends it back to the bowler
quick, on a good length, angling in towards off stump, defended back to the bowler
now he strides out of his crease and reaches the pitch of the ball to whip it away towards deep midwicket

Afridi gets another. Maxwell goes for the slog-sweep, but he's only managed to pick out Umar Amin, who runs to his left from deep square leg and takes a superb diving catch. Just about managed to hold on even though he landed on his elbows and the ball threatened to pop out
works this length ball off the stumps, towards square leg
length ball on the stumps, worked with the turn towards square leg
back of a length on off stump, defended into the off side
walks across his stumps, and defends back to the bowler
back of a length now, and he shuffles across to tuck it away towards square leg
on the pads, and Hughes is off the mark with a little clip towards midwicket
fullish ball on off stump, clipped to short midwicket
back of a length, a bit of width outside off, punched to deep cover point
down the pitch, clipped off the toes towards short midwicket, where Anwar dives to his right but can't stop cleanly
shuffles across as this turns in from outside off and defends from the crease
full and wide, steered away backward of point
back of a length, punched to cover
tossed up outside off, ends up as a full-toss that Smith hits uppishly, just wide of short extra cover, down to long off
drags this down the leg side, and Smith tucks it away towards deep square leg
angled in towards off from wide of a crease, Smith comes forward and coaxes it towards point
down the pitch now, and he drives down to long-on to bring up his fifty
full, whipped from middle and off to short midwicket
down the pitch now, clipped down to long on
down the pitch again, pushed with a straight bat to long-off
slants this across Hughes, who dabs it with the angle to backward point
worked away to deep backward square leg
down the pitch, clipped down to wide long-on
down the pitch now, turns this towards short midwicket
doesn't turn in as far as he expected from outside off, turned his bat face too quickly, and the outside edge runs away to short third man
full and wide, driven to cover point, who's standing on the edge of the circle
turns it in from outside off, tucked with the turn to deep square leg for one
makes room and pushes the length ball towards cover
takes a step down now and pushes it back
slightly shorter towards middle and leg, pushed down to long-on for one
moves across and this one hardly turned after pitching outside off, Hughes defended delicately
leans forward and blocks the length delivery from outside off
short ball angled across towards off, pulled to midwicket
cramped for room as Hughes moves across a bit, looks to pull but the ball doesn't bounce as much and moves in to hit him around the waist

loud appeal and Tanvir gets him! Hughes has reviewed it. The ball swung in after pitching outside off, hit him on the knee roll in front of the off stump and that would have hit the stumps, says the ball-tracking technology. Hughes has to walk back
length delivery outside off is angled across, Haddin lets it go
touch wider outside off, Haddin leans forward and pushes to cover
on leg and was headed to middle, Haddin goes back and tucks it on the leg side for one
slightly full and angling across outside off, pushed to cover
edged but that fell short of the keeper! Back of length outside off, Haddin went for the cut and got an inside edge but that didn't carry
on length outside off with the angle, helps it to third man for one
bit of extra bounce after it pitched on middle, moved away and surprised Smith as he defended it to cover

full on off now, driven down to mid-on, and Haddin is a few feet outside the crease. The fielder - Anwar Ali - was alert to spot that and rocketed a flat throw for a direct hit. It's gone to the third umpire and Haddin is a few inches short. A dismissal made out of nothing, with full credit to the fielder
length delivery on the off stump, turned a bit wide of mid-on for one and he keeps strike
swings it across a bit from outside off, pushed to cover point off the front foot
touch shorter just outside off, Smith goes back in the crease and defends it back
on length now close to off, no room whatsoever and he defends again
tad shorter on similar line close to off, Smith defends to short cover now
strays towards middle and leg, and it's full, flicked to deep square leg for one
tight line and length on off stump, Faulkner blocks it back
charges down, Babar pitches it shorter and it's pushed to cover
towards the pads now and it's clipped to backward square leg
much fuller on off stump, driven down to long-off for one
flights it on length on off, Faulkner leans forward and blocks
bit shorter and coming in towards off, he stays back and pushes to cover
slightly short on off and it's turned wide of midwicket for one
back of length around off, whipped down to mid-on
fuller outside off and it's driven sweetly, but straight to cover
shorter outside off, Faulkner stays back and taps it to cover point
angled towards the pads now, flicked to deep midwicket for one
moves across for the short of length delivery outside off and pulls it around to deep backward square leg
fuller and angling in, flicked straight to midwicket
pretty slow and drifting in towards middle, pushed down easily to long-on
flighted on off, defends it back to the bowler
shorter towards the leg stump, Faulkner gets it to short fine leg off the pad
flighted well outside off, pushed a bit wide of cover for one
on length on middle and leg, he goes back and tucks it to deep backward square leg for one
length delivery outside off, pushed with a straight bat to cover
short of length towards middle, Smith moves across and whips it past short fine leg for a four in the gap. He knows there has been a drought of boundaries and runs, both
on length outside off now, helped to third man for one
slightly short of length on off stump, turned to midwicket
full on off now, pushed down to long-on for one off the front foot
makes room towards the leg side, Anwar pitches it short and a swish is cut at cover point by a dive for one
short of length outside off, Faulkner cuts hard but gets a bottom edge towards point
drifts one full towards the leg stump, he comes down and drives to long-on
goes back to whip the ball to leg but gets it on the body after some turn
this one turns in too and Faulkner tucks it on the leg side
legspinner on length outside off, cut off the back foot to sweeper cover
googly comes in from outside off, keeps low and Faulkner misses while trying to cut
tucked to square leg for one run
flighted outside off, defends with a forward lean to cover
angles it in from around off, Faulkner looks to turn it to leg but gets it on his pad
leans forward and pushes to cover again, no room again
on length on middle and leg, turned finally for one to deep midwicket
comes down a track and pushes it a bit wide of long-on to come back for two
well outside off on length, Smith wants to sweep but can't connect
length delivery angled across, swishes it towards cover for one
Irfan appeals for lbw as Smith made room to slog but the slower delivery deceived him and he was hit on the pads well outside leg
full toss just outside off, turned away to deep midwicket for one
short of length outside leg stump, he makes room and tucks it to third man for two
full outside off, he makes some room and crunches a drive through covers, wide of deep point in the gap for two
finally a boundary! It was slower and coming towards the stumps from outside leg, Faulkner nearly went down on a knee and slogged it to the wide long-on boundary for a four
short and wide, Smith makes room to cut and it's been called a no ball because Tanvir's back foot touched the return crease
he's bowled'im as Smith wanted to slog it to the leg side and the full delivery crashed onto the stumps
slightly shorter and angled in, he swats it wide of deep midwicket for two
short and wide outside off, Smith nicely pulled it without much force gently towards deep midwicket to collect two more
bowled again, this time he has to go! Smith charged down with some room and wanted to smash it over the covers but missed it and the ball knocked over the base of off stump
swinging full toss outside off, thick edge rolls down to third man
angled in towards the pads, he wants to tuck it to leg but gets it on the pads
attempted yorker is a low full toss on leg, pushed down to mid-on
another low full toss on middle, swished away towards deep backward point for two
low full toss number 3, it's outside off and is pushed to cover
full delivery just outside off, he makes room and drives to deep point
higher full toss outside off, Starc pushes it back to the bowler
nearly in the block hole around off, he digs it out to long-on and wants two, but there's time only for one as Babar gets to it quickly
offspinner form outside leg towards the pads, he defends it on leg
closer to the stumps, inside edge off the thigh pad goes to third man for one
slightly shorter and it's turned off the back foot to deep midwicket gently, so that it doesn't reach the fielder quickly and then run two
cut off the back foot towards backward point where Fawad dives to stop it
falls safe! Flighted googly on leg, he flicked it but the googly took a top edge and went very high between mid-off and long-off. No fielder could get there on time
turned to backward square leg off the back foot for one
bouncer on the leg stump and coming in, he ducks under it
makes room, Irfan pitches it short again, Faulkner looked to cut but missed it
attempted yorker is a low full toss on the pads and Faulkner lofts it high in the air and in the gap wide of long-on for two
he wants a six and connects to get one! This was pitched up and he slogged it well over the long-on boundary for a clean six to clear long-on
low full toss is too wide outside off for a wide

excellent work from Irfan. He first bowled a slower one on back of length by rolling his fingers over this one, Faulkner could not connect well and the ball went back towards the bowler. Starc was well outside the crease by now, Irfan is on the ground while stopping the ball and turns and gets a direct hit
full on off and midle, tapped wide of cover for one and he keeps strike

gets a wicket first ball! Short of length ball was angled in, Faulkner pulled it but this ground is big and the blow was not that powerful, Umar Amin at deep midwicket takes a few steps in to catch it
full and just outside off, pushed down the ground towards mid-off for one
makes room and slices the full delivery from elg stump to point for one
low and slow full toss outside off, it's mistimed down the ground towards long-on who runs to his left and throws at the keeper's end. They come back for two
makes room for the ball that's angling in, slogged down to long-on for two more
has he got enough? He makes room to loft the full delivery from outside off to the extra cover region in the air, there's nobody in the deep and that rolls away for four

inn2.comm: length ball to start with, angling towards off stump, and maybe some late inward movement to cramp Shehzad, who tucks it away towards midwicket
slants it a little further across, outside off stump, and Shehzad lets it go
back of a length, and Shehzad shuffles across to defend off the back foot
a little fuller and wider, and Shehzad leaves again
full and even wider this time, and Shehzad won't nibble at those
back of a length outside off, and he stands up tall and punches to short cover. Starc starts with a maiden
sharp inward movement from outside off towards Sarfraz's midriff, and he hurriedly jams his bat down to plonk it into the leg side
a bit of movement in again, cramping Sarfraz from back of a length. He tucks it away to short midwicket
width this time outside off, and he steers this nicely off the back foot to the right of third man. Slips while turning at the non-striker's end, so they can't take the second run
length ball outside off, comes forward and plays a defensive push to short cover
fuller now, swinging in towards off stump, and Shehzad plays a firm push back to the bowler
full outside off, driven to the right of Maxwell at point
back of a length, and Sarfraz shuffles across, possibly looking to work that leg side, but the angle forces him to poke it back to the bowler
back of a length just outside off, keeps a touch low maybe, and Sarfraz squats a little while defending into the off side
a little short, and Sarfraz stands tall and punches that away to the right of third man
full outside off, and he steers this past the left hand of a diving Maxwell at backward point
full, on the pads, clipped away very neatly to the left of deep backward square leg
looks to bowl the bouncer and loses his action a touch, sending this down the leg side
length ball on middle stump, defended back to the bowler
back of a length outside off, another leave from Shehzad
back of a length outside off, decent carry through to Haddin as Shehzad leaves again
this time he swishes at the ball outside off, and the ball beats the outside edge of his angled bat
back of a length, a bit more width this time, and he slaps it away to the right of third man
length ball outside off, and Sarfraz leans into it and times it beautifully through cover
similar delivery, a little closer to off stump, and he drives it straighter, to the left of mid-off
looks to play another cover drive, but the feet don't go anywhere, and the left-arm angle causes him to edge that down to third man
back of a length, angling across. Didn't really come onto Shehzad, who waited a long time to play that back-foot defensive prod
full and wide, Shehzad doesn't quite get close enough to the ball to drive, and the ball bounces down into the pitch
full on off stump, defended to mid-on
short, rising ball, and he swivels and pulls this away towards the vacant deep midwicket region. He didn't really time that, and it stops well short of the boundary
length ball angling across towards off stump, defended into the off side
back of a length on off stump, worked away wristily to short midwicket
a touch fuller now, angling in towards off stump. Shehzad stays on the back foot and defends towards mid-on
length ball on off stump, Shehzad shuffles across and works it with the angle past short midwicket
full outside off, drives to the left of mid-off and sets off immediately for the single. Warner has to run around the ball to throw, and Shehzad makes his crease comfortably
back of a length, angling in towards leg stump, tucked away to deep backward square leg
fullish ball angling in towards middle stump, clipped to mid-on
once again down the leg side, and Shehzad skips across his crease to earn his team a wide
back of a length outside off, steered to backward point
down the leg side once more, but this time it clipped Sarfraz's thigh pad as he looked to glance to fine leg
back of a length, a bit of shape in towards middle stump, defended towards mid-off
a bit of width again and Sarfraz looks to use the pace and angle to steer it wide of backward point, and hits it straight to the fielder
full now, and he presses forward to drive to cover
on the pads now, and he works it away to deep backward square leg
starts off by drifting onto the pads, and Sarfraz flicks it away to deep backward square leg
full outside off, and Shehzad punches firmly down the ground but is denied by Sarfraz, who couldn't get out of the way of the shot quickly enough
full, wide, and Shehzad frees his arms and crashes it away to the left of cover
this is a little shorter but just as wide, and Shehzad drills the ball through the same gap, only this one's off the back foot. This is a terrible start from Faulkner
fuller now, width again, and Shehzad drives to the right of the cover fielder
full outside off, angling in, and Shehzad comes forward to defend back to the bowler
full and leg-stumpish, and Sarfraz flicks it away to deep square leg
down the track, doesn't quite reach the pitch of the ball, and adjusts to defend into the covers
down the leg side, and Shehzad sweeps fine, to the right of deep backward square leg
length ball on the pads, tucked away towards deep backward square leg
quickish now, on middle stump, and Shehzad was looking to make room and drive inside out but it was too quick to do that and he defended towards cover in the end
down the pitch now and he lifts this over the infield to send it rolling away to the deep midwicket boundary
back of a length, angling in towards Shehzad's ribcage, and he gets on his toes to defend towards short midwicket
length ball, angling in towards off stump, defended to mid-off
down the track and Faulkner follows him. Looks to club that over the leg side but can only inside-edge it onto his left leg
length ball angling in towards off stump, pushed to mid-off
dropped! Shehzad came down the track again and played a poor shot, smacking it straight into mid-on's hands, but Sean Abbott, the substitute fielder, couldn't hold on
down the track again and this time he makes room and lofts gloriously over extra cover
full, down the leg side, and the ball runs away wide of Haddin's gloves as he shuffles across to collect
full, leg-stumpish, clipped to deep midwicket
fullish ball on the pads, and Warner dives to his left at square leg to cut off that flick
down the pitch now, and he plays a checked drive to long-on
goes deep in his crease to the length ball and works the ball away to deep midwicket
back of a length again, and he goes on the back foot to work it leg side but Warner is in the way again
a little fuller, and he clips it away to deep midwicket
bowled him! Shehzad made room to cut, but that wasn't short enough, and it went with the angle and crashed into middle and off
tossed up on off stump, driven to short cover
length ball on off, turns away a decent amount, and he waits on it and dabs it towards point
fuller, on middle stump, defended watchfully off the front foot
short, wide, and Shafiq rocks back and crashes it away through the gap between point and cover
fuller now, outside off, and he comes forward and defends towards point
back of a length on off stump, and Sarfraz shuffles across to work the ball to deep backward square leg
back of a length, angling down the leg side, Shafiq tucks it away towards square leg
back of a length on middle stump, clipped to deep square leg
back of a length, angling in, and he pokes at the ball outside off and the inside-edge cannons into his pads
back of a length, a bit straighter, defended back to the bowler
back of a length outside off, guided to third man with an open face
full on middle and leg, driven past the diving bowler to long-on
fullish ball on off stump, defended with soft hands to backward point
length ball on off stump, defended to short cover

turn now, quick turn from back of a length and beats Sarfraz's bat as he looks to prod it away through the off side. Haddin whipped the bails off and appealed, and they go up to the third umpire. Sarfraz did lift his foot, but he brought it down just in time
fuller now, and he gets his front foot out and drives to the right of point
down the pitch now and Shafiq drives to long-off
whipped in the air but the ball lands short of short midwicket
length ball on off stump, punched to mid-on
back of a length outside off, punched to short cover
length ball, angling in and giving no room. Shafiq pushes it to mid-on
angle brings it into the pads now, and he tucks it away to deep square leg
back of a length, angling in towards off, and Sarfraz lets it come to him and dabs it towards third man
length ball on the stumps, and Sarfraz loves to sweep, hits that firmly down to deep backward square leg
only a touch short, and he's back in his crease in a flash but can't beat short cover with that slap
down the pitch now and Doherty bowls it quick and flat, defended back to the bowler
shortish ball outside off, and he cuts it to point, who's standing on the edge of the circle
length ball on middle stump, Sarfraz makes room and dabs it to point
short ball, and Shafiq pulls it away over short midwicket. Hughes sprints a long way from long-on and dives, but only succeeds in dragging himself and the ball over the rope
short ball on off stump, pulled away to deep square leg
length ball on off stump, and Shafiq hits it back to the bowler, not quite managing to time that firm drive down the ground
back of a length now, and Shafiq pokes it back to the bowler
back of a length on off stump, and Shafiq pulls it away to deep midwicket
back of a length on off stump, poked away to point
length ball on off stump, and Sarfraz lets it come to him and guides it to third man

sweeps from the stumps again, towards deep midwicket. Starc ran to his left from deep backward square and let rip a flat throw to the keeper as the batsmen looked to take him on and run a second. Sarfraz dives into his crease, but his bat crosses the line a crucial instant after Haddin whips the bails off
tossed up around off on length, Fawad tucks it to midwicket
leans forward and blocks it outside off
slightly short of length outside off, Fawad waits for it and guides to short third man

that's another wicket, but the umpires are going up! Fawad swept it fine down the leg side, Smith was at first slip and he ran like a hare towards leg slip in anticipation just after the ball was delivered and takes what looks like an easy catch at leg slip. Great anticipation after he saw Fawad get into position to sweep. The umpires have ruled him out, Fawad waited for a long time at the boundary and eventually walked out
another chance, umpire goes up for stumping! Beaten by the turn outside off with a forward push, Haddin whips the bails off but his back toe is just inside the crease
back of length outside off, he pokes and misses as it shapes away
persists outside off and this one's pushed down towards mid-off
short ball, he pulls and a top edge flies right over Haddin for two in the gap
coming in from back of length towards off, he defends it back
short ball angled in, and it goes off the glove down the leg side just wide of Haddin's left glove as he leapt full length for that
back of length outside off, he lets it go
fullish outside off, driven firmly to cover
shorter on the stumps and he defends on the leg side
on length on middle and turning towards off, keeps a bit low as he whips it down to mid-on
goes on the back foot again and that's turned past midwicket against the turn to get off the mark
shorter and much wider, cut off the back foot to long-off
bit of flight on middle and leg, Maqsood defends it back
back of length outside off, driven off the front foot to point where Maxwell dives to his right and stops
shorter outside off, guides it late towards third man for one
similar length well outside off, punched off the back foot to deep backward point for two
brings it closer to off stump from short of length, Maqsood helps it to midwicket
bangs in another short one outside off, the batsman defends off the toes
stays back and cuts it late towards third man but backward point dives to his left and stops it
slow through the air around middle, he comes down and blocks
on length around off, waits for it to turn and cuts towards cover point
flighted on middle with turn, pushed to point with a forward lean
length delivery on off with away turn, cuts off the back foot to cover
comes down a step and drives the length ball with the turn to short cover
flighted on middle, Shaifq stays in and defends. That's a maiden
flighted and full outside off, drives it firmly down to long-off
shorter outside off, cuts off the back foot to cover after the turn
another cut off the back foot as it pitched closer to off, goes to deep point
slightly quicker outside off, he looks to cut it late and misses
flighted on the pads, driven down to mid-on
shorter and wider outside off, pulled off the back foot to long-on
comes down the track and he whips it with his wrists against the turn from middle stump to the midwicket boundary for a four in the gap. Excellent shot
makes some room to push it down past short cover for one
flatter on off, pushed to mid-on against the turn
flighted on middle and leg, flicked firmly straight to midwicket
flighted on leg stump, driven down to long-on for one
drifts down the leg side for a wide past the pads
flighted outside off, he leans forward and blocks it
flighted and full on middle, drives it down to long-off
on length outside off and turning away, chops it off the back foot to deep point
fuller outside off, slices it late to backward point
straighter one on middle stump, pushed back to the bowler
flighted again, smashed back and the ball flies towards cover after hitting the non-striker's bat
outside off on length, pushed back to the bowler
turning it in from middle, tucked to square leg
on middle again, tucked off the back foot to deep midwicket
fuller outside off, drives it down to long-off
goes back and chops it late to point
flighted on the leg stump, flicked straight to midwicket
on middle and he goes back again to whip it straight to midwicket
angles it in from outside off, tucked off the back foot to backward square leg
slightly fuller towards off stump, driven down to mid-on
angled towards the pads now, it hits the pads and goes towards midwicket or a leg bye
the angle is too much and that one goes past the batsman, past the keeper and goes down leg for four
fuller on the middle stump, clipped to deep backward square leg for one
in the block hole on off, Sohaib digs it back to the bowler
nearly a yorker on middle and leg, flicked to deep midwicket for one
chipped in the air past the bowler to long-on for one
turns with a lean to midwicket
gets into position early and sweeps it fine down leg for two runs
pushes off the front foot towards off but thick inside edge goes to the leg side
full on the pads and Shafiq knows where the gap is. He goes down on a knee and sweeps it in the air to the backward square leg area for four
spins it well down leg for a wide
almost going for another wide, swatted to fine leg for one
on length outside off with the angle, left alone
length delivery outside off again, chopped straight to backward point
pitches it a touch shorter, he looked to cut it late but missed the edge
on length on the pads now, clipped to midwicket
wide full toss outside off, steered to deep point for one
on the pads again, tucked down to fine leg for one more
pitched outside off and that's lofted towards sweeper cover for one and that's the 50 stand
comes down a step to push it down, Doherty gets a hand that goes towards cover
goes on the back foot to cut but that was very close to middle stump. He did get bat on it
turned away to the leg side now against the turn towards square leg
full in the zone and Sohaib slogs it taking the aerial route to the wide long on area by going down on a knee
towards middle and leg on length, nearly scooped to cover off the front foot. Reaches the fielder after a bounce
short of length towards off and middle, defends it to mid-on
angled in sharply from outside off, doesn't have enough room to put it away on the leg side
short, pulled powerfully to the leg side and Warner in the deep dives to his right at deep backward square leg and throws it back immediately
defends the back of length delivery from outside off back to the bowler
cuts it in from outside off, he defends it again
pulled in the air, Warner is in the deep but falls well short of him, and wide too, as he runs to his right and cuts it to one
flattish outside off, he comes down and defends it back
bit shorter and on middle stump and the tall man rocks back to smack it over the midwicket boundary for six! He got in position very early
swishes outside off and thick outside edge rolls away towards third man for two
on the other side now - four more! He got some room outside off and lofted it inside out in the gap between long off and sweeper cover
another excellent shot, it won't go for four though. Got little room outside off and it was chopped wide of deep point for two in the gap
leans forward and defends the length delivery back to the bowler

cut off the back foot outside off, it's rolling away to deep backward point and Doherty slides to his right to cut it in, but the ball still rolls away and might have hit his cap which fell behind him when he was sliding. Umpire says it's three runs
back of length and coming in, he defends towards cover
punches the short of length ball around off back to the bowler
pulled again, the short ball gets Maqsood and Warner takes it easily running in from deep midwicket. Richardson bowled the scrambled seam outside off and Maqsood didn't get the distance on that one
short ball again, goes over the batsman towards the leg side as he ducks
short of length and angled in, tucked away to fine leg for one and he keeps strike
flighted on leg, drives it down to long-on for one
flighted around off, he drives it wide of cover point to get off the mark
flighted just outside leg, clipped towards backward square leg
flighted and full outside off, drives off the front foot to point
flight and drift towards middle stump, pushed down the ground to long-off
comes down the track and tucks it with the turn to long-on to bring up his fifty
short ball angled in, he wants to pull but it doesn't bounce so much and he gets hit around the groin

angled in from wide of the crease, Shafiq was stuck on the crease, and the break has given Australia a breakthrough! Shafiq checks with Amin whether he should review, and Amin says no, and you can see why he said that. It struck him below the knee-roll, on the crease, in front of middle stump.
greets him with a bouncer, and Afridi ducks under it
back of a length, angling across, and Afridi defends with soft hands, off the back foot
another bouncer, outside the line of off stump, Afridi lets it go
back of a length, angling in towards off stump, and that's a compact-looking backfoot defensive shot
length ball outside off, fuller than the previous one, and Afridi shows he can defend solidly off the front foot too
slants this into the pads, and Amin works it towards midwicket
lovely delivery, angling across Afridi and leaving him slightly off the pitch. He pokes and he's beaten
fuller now, on off stump, and it's driven down to the man at deep cover
back of a length, angling in towards off stump, blocked off the back foot, back to the bowler
looks to get it a little fuller and straighter, and overdoes the straighter, slanting it down the leg side
back of a length, lovely off-stump line, no room at all, and Amin can only defend it to the bowler
aaaand again. This one's even wider down the leg side
back of a length and a bit of bounce outside off. Amin pokes at it with no footwork and the ball beats his edge
back of a length outside off, punched to deep cover
back of a length outside off, shuffles across and defends to point
a bit of extra bounce outside off and Amin plays that no-footwork prod again. The outside edge runs away towards third man
fuller now, a little closer to off stump, and he comes forward and pushes towards mid-off
full again, a bigger stride now to drive to the right of mid-off
on the pads, and he gets a leg bye to short fine leg as he misses connecting with the flick
what a shot! That was a back of a length ball outside off, and he simply shuffled across and hoicked that away with a flick of the wrist wide of the short fine leg fielder
short, wide, cut straight to Maxwell at point
full now, angling in towards middle stump. Afridi stays leg-side of the ball and defends towards cover

short outside off, and that's a familiar sight to anyone who knows Afridi. The attempted pull, the top edge, the sky-high catch to mid-on running to his left. That was the effort ball from Richardson, and well directed too, rising above Afridi's right shoulder
length ball in the corridor outside off, and it straightens just a touch and beats the outside edge as Anwar pokes uncertainly at it
back of a length outside off, Anwar lets it go through to the keeper
short, a bit of width, and that's punched very sweetly into the gap at extra cover
length ball on off stump, Anwar defends after coming halfway forward
back of a length, starts on leg and middle, but Anwar is wary of the angle across and plays with a full face towards cover
wider now, and Anwar lets it go outside off
full and leg-stumpish. Anwar misses the flick and the ball ricochets off his pad towards square leg
back of a length outside off, and that's a good-looking punch to short cover
fullish ball, angling in, and Anwar comes forward to push to cover
back of a length now, and he defends it back towards the bowler
a touch straighter now, and he nurdles it away towards short midwicket
slower yorker on off and middle, worked away towards midwicket
back of a length on off, and he waits and dabs it away towards point
length ball outside off, and Anwar hits it down the ground, over the bowler's head, with a straight bat and a full extension of the arms, and the ball sails over the long-on boundary
full and flat, fired in towards off stump, and he opens his bat face to jab that away towards point
full again, but slanting down the leg side, and he tickles it away towards short fine leg
full on off stump, pushed back to the bowler
full outside off, steered to point
goes back as Maxwell angles this across, and looks to push it through cover, but the ball goes with the angle and beats his edge. It ricochets off Haddin and runs away towards fine leg
fuller this time, and he comes forward and drives firmly to the left of the bowler, and Maxwell dives full-length to cut off the ball
short ball, and Amin swivels to pull this to the left of the man at deep midwicket
on the pads now, and he clips it away towards deep square leg
slower ball, angled in towards off stump. Anwar comes forward and defends back to the bowler
length ball, angled towards middle and leg, and he pushes it down the ground to long-on
short ball, and he times this pull beautifully to beat the deep square leg fielder haring around the boundary and diving full-length to his right. Could have done better, Sean Abbott
slower ball, full on leg stump, clipped down to deep backward square leg
fullish ball, angling in, and he comes forward and drives to mid-off
on middle stump now, and Amin flicks it away to deep backward square leg
back of a length, worked off the hips into the vacant midwicket region
back of a length, angling in and tucking him up for room, and Amin is forced to defend back to the bowler
short ball on off stump, and he rides the bounce and steers it away to the left of third man to bring up Pakistan's 200
full and wide, and it was there to drive, but it bounced crazily, beat his edge, and Haddin had to jump up and parry the ball over his head
fullish ball outside off, driven to mid-off
shortish ball, angling in and rising towards the midriff. He jumps to get on top of the bounce and nudges it away towards fine leg
full and wide, and he drives this firmly and short cover does well to stop that diving to his left
full again, driven down to mid-off. Went hard at it and didn't time it
short outside off, and he gets on top of the bounce and bunts it down to third man
short ball, and Amin looks at the umpire after he ducks under it, wondering if it might be called wide for height. It isn't
length ball on the pads, clipped to midwicket
very full outside off, and the ball sneaks under Anwar's bat as he looks to jab it away through the off side
length ball on leg stump, gets an inside edge that hits the pad and dribbles towards midwicket as he looks to drive down the ground
bowled him! That was full, and it came in late and sneaked through the gap between Amin's bat and pad and crashed into off stump. He was looking to drive that through cover
and that's a welcome run for Pakistan, Starc angling one too far down the leg side
full outside off, driven to short cover with a checked follow-through
back of a length outside off, and he defends off the back foot, playing extremely late, and the ball bounces through to the keeper
back of a length outside off, guided down to third man
back of a length, angling across towards off stump, poked away to point
back of a length on off stump, defended to point off the back foot. Looked quite compact there
on the pads now, and it's clipped away towards deep backward square leg
length ball outside off, super front-foot stride out to defend into the covers
a little wider outside off now, and Tanvir drives to short cover
slants this across outside off, not quite up there to drive, and he goes after it and slices it at a catchable height to Maxwell at backward point
short ball first up, and Babar ducks hurriedly under it

oh my. Faulkner might have fluffed up an easy run out, or has he? That was back of a length, and Babar pushed it towards cover point. Maxwell ran from backward point and threw to the bowler. Both batsmen had set off, and the run simply wasn't on. When Faulkner collected, Babar was a long way from the stumps. He swished at the stumps with the ball and missed first time, and then had to go through the process again. He hit, and replays show Babar was still an inch short of his crease. But they didn't go up to the third umpire!
full now, and he drives this down to long-on
back of a length now, and he gets on his toes and works it off his ribcage down to the fine leg boundary
back of a length on off stump, and he dabs it away to third man
fullish ball on off stump, driven into the covers
on the pads now, and it's worked away to square leg
tossed up on off stump, in the blockhole, and he looks to flick but can only hit it into his own boot
looks to sweep from outside off and misses, and is hit on the front pad

tossed up on off stump, and he's simply extended his arms to send that over the rope at long-off. There were a few iceboxes beyond the boundary, and Smith ran back and landed on one of them as he dived over the rope in a desperate attempt to catch that. Could have easily hurt himself
quickish ball outside off, pushed into the off side
pushed through on off stump, worked away to long-on past Doherty, who ran to his right and dived to try and save the single
length ball on off stump, worked away to deep backward square leg
full on middle and leg, worked away towards deep square leg
back of a length, goes with the angle towards middle and leg, and Babar looks to make room and punch through cover and gets a lucky edge that runs away towards the third man boundary
length ball on off stump, pushed to mid-on
down the pitch, and he's drilled that through the short cover fielder. Long-off runs around to his left and keeps it down to two
looks for the big slog sweep from outside off, misses, is hit on the midriff
oh, my. What have you done, Sohail Tanvir? Maxwell fired that in flat and full, and Tanvir swung across the line again. Tanvir missed, Maxwell hit
length ball angled across, and Irfan leans forward, threatening to fall over, and blocks
goes for the big slog and misses, but this was bowled wide outside off so he survives
tosses it up outside off once again, and Irfan swings and misses once again
Maxwell has won it for Australia! That was on the stumps and Irfan swung hard at it. The ball took his outside edge and looped in the air and the man at cover took a simple catch
